## Step 3: Using the new variables $u$ and $v$, we can rewrite the expression as follows:
\begin{align*}
\sqrt{x^2 + 400} + \sqrt{y^2 + 900} + \sqrt{x^2 + y^2 - 80x - 100y + 4100} &= \sqrt{\left(x + \frac{1}{2}y\right)^2 + 400} + \sqrt{\left(x - \frac{1}{2}y\right)^2 + 900} \\
&\quad + \sqrt{\left(x + \frac{1}{2}y\right)^2 + \left(x - \frac{1}{2}y\right)^2 - 80\left(x + \frac{1}{2}y\right) - 100\left(x - \frac{1}{2}y\right) + 4100} \\
&= \sqrt{u^2 + 400} + \sqrt{v^2 + 900} + \sqrt{2u^2 - 80u - 100v + 4100}
\end{align*}

## Step 5: Let's rewrite the expression $\sqrt{2u^2 - 80u - 100v + 4100}$ as follows:
\begin{align*}
\sqrt{2u^2 - 80u - 100v + 4100} &= \sqrt{2\left(u^2 - 40u + 100\right) - 100v + 4100} \\
&= \sqrt{2\left(u - 20\right)^2 + 4100 - 100v} \\
&= \sqrt{2\left(u - 20\right)^2 - 100\left(v - 40\right)}
\end{align*}
